e credit balances for this row.","pos":[20193,20237]},{"pos":[20244,20287],"content":"Column Restriction cell in a row definition","linkify":"Column Restriction cell in a row definition","nodes":[{"content":"Column Restriction cell in a row definition","pos":[0,43]}]},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Column Restriction<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> cell in a row definition has multiple purposes.","pos":[20288,20362],"source":"The **Column Restriction** cell in a row definition has multiple purposes."},{"content":"Depending on the type of row, you can use the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Column Restriction<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> cell to specify one of the following functions:","pos":[20363,20479],"source":" Depending on the type of row, you can use the **Column Restriction** cell to specify one of the following functions:"},{"content":"The cell can limit the printing of row amounts to a specific column.","pos":[20485,20553]},{"content":"This function is useful if you're creating a tabular balance sheet.","pos":[20554,20621]},{"content":"The cell can specify the column of amounts to sort.","pos":[20626,20677]},{"pos":[20682,20729],"content":"Using a calculation formula in a row definition","linkify":"Using a calculation formula in a row definition","nodes":[{"content":"Using a calculation formula in a row definition","pos":[0,47]}]},{"content":"A calculation formula in a row definition can include the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt><ph id=\"ph1\">+</ph><ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt><ph id=\"ph2\">-</ph><ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>, <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt><ph id=\"ph3\">\\*</ph><ept id=\"p3\">**</ept>, and <bpt id=\"p4\">**</bpt><ph id=\"ph4\">/</ph><ept id=\"p4\">**</ept> operators, and also <bpt id=\"p5\">**</bpt>IF/THEN/ELSE<ept id=\"p5\">**</ept> statements.","pos":[20730,20868],"source":"A calculation formula in a row definition can include the **+**, **-**, **\\***, and **/** operators, and also **IF/THEN/ELSE** statements."},{"content":"Additionally, a calculation