 in row 330, you can use the row total formula **100+330** or the calculation formula **@100+@330**."},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> You must use an at sign (@) before every row code that you use in a calculation formula.","pos":[21846,21944],"source":"**Note:** You must use an at sign (@) before every row code that you use in a calculation formula."},{"content":"Otherwise, the number is read as an absolute amount.","pos":[21945,21997]},{"content":"For example, the formula <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt><ph id=\"ph1\">@100</ph>+330<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> adds USD 330 to the amount in row 100.","pos":[21998,22074],"source":" For example, the formula **@100+330** adds USD 330 to the amount in row 100."},{"content":"When you reference a column in a calculation formula, an at sign (@) isn't required.","pos":[22075,22159]},{"pos":[22165,22193],"content":"Create a calculation formula","linkify":"Create a calculation formula","nodes":[{"content":"Create a calculation formula","pos":[0,28]}]},{"pos":[22199,22289],"content":"In Report Designer, click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Row Definitions<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, and then open the row definition to modify.","source":"In Report Designer, click **Row Definitions**, and then open the row definition to modify."},{"pos":[22294,22357],"content":"Double-click the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Format Code<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> cell, and then select <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>CAL<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>.","source":"Double-click the **Format Code** cell, and then select **CAL**."},{"pos":[22362,22436],"content":"In the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Related Formulas/Rows/Units<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> cell, type the calculation formula.","source":"In the **Related Formulas/Rows/Units** cell, type the calculation formula."},{"pos":[22442,22492],"content":"Example of a calculation formula for specific rows","linkify":"Example of a calculation formula for specific rows","nodes":[{"content":"Example of a calculation formula for specif