urce":"@130\\*.75"},{"content":"For every column, the value in row 130 is multiplied by 0.75.","pos":[26430,26491]},{"content":"The result is then put in the current row of every column.","pos":[26492,26550]},{"content":"B=<ph id=\"ph1\">@130</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">\\*</ph>.75","pos":[26555,26566],"source":"B=@130\\*.75"},{"content":"The same calculation is performed only on column B.","pos":[26580,26631]},{"content":"A,B,C=(<ph id=\"ph1\">@100/</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">@130</ph>)<ph id=\"ph3\">\\*</ph>.75","pos":[26705,26727],"source":"A,B,C=(@100/@130)\\*.75"},{"content":"A=(A.100/A.130)<ph id=\"ph1\">\\*</ph>.75 B=(B.100/B.130)<ph id=\"ph2\">\\*</ph>.75 C=(C.100/C.130)<ph id=\"ph3\">\\*</ph>.75","pos":[26730,26792],"source":"A=(A.100/A.130)\\*.75 B=(B.100/B.130)\\*.75 C=(C.100/C.130)\\*.75"},{"pos":[26858,26901],"content":"IF/THEN/ELSE statements in a row definition","linkify":"IF/THEN/ELSE statements in a row definition","nodes":[{"content":"IF/THEN/ELSE statements in a row definition","pos":[0,43]}]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IF/THEN/ELSE<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> statements can be added to any valid calculation and used with the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>CAL<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> format.","pos":[26903,27002],"source":"**IF/THEN/ELSE** statements can be added to any valid calculation and used with the **CAL** format."},{"content":"You enter <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IF/THEN/ELSE<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> calculation formulas in the cell in the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Related Formulas/Rows/Units<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> column.","pos":[27003,27109],"source":" You enter **IF/THEN/ELSE** calculation formulas in the cell in the **Related Formulas/Rows/Units** column."},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IF/THEN/ELSE<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> calculation formulas use the following format: IF <ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;lt;</ph>true/false statement<ph id=\"ph2\">&amp;gt;</ph> THEN <ph id=\"ph3\">&amp;lt;</ph>formula<ph id=\"ph4\">&amp;gt;</ph> ELSE <ph id=\"ph5\">&amp;lt;</ph>formula<ph id=\"ph6\">&amp;gt;</ph> The <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>ELSE <ph id=\"ph7\">&amp;lt;</ph>formula<ph id=\"ph8\">&amp;gt;</ph><ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> part of the statement is optional.","pos":[27110,27311],"source":"**IF/THEN/ELSE** calculation formulas use the following format: IF &lt;true/false statement&gt; THEN &lt;formula&gt; ELSE &lt;formula&gt; The **ELSE &lt;formula&gt;** part of the statement is optional."},{"pos":[27318,27331],"content":"IF statements","linkify":"IF statements","nodes":[{"content":"IF statements","pos":[0,13]}]},{"content":"The statement that follows the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IF<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> statement can be any statement that can be evaluated as true or false.","pos":[27333,27441],"source":"The statement that follows the **IF** statement can be any statement that can be evaluated as true or false."},{"content":"The statement that follows the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IF<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> statement might involve a simple evaluation, or it might be a complex statement that can contain multiple expressions.","pos":[27442,27598],"source":" The statement that follows the **IF** statement might involve a simple evaluation, or it might be a complex statement that can contain multiple expressions."},{"content":"Here are some examples:","pos":[27599,27622]},{"pos":[27628,27665],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IF A.200<ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;gt;</ph>0<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> (Simple evaluation)","source":"**IF A.200&gt;0** (Simple evaluation)"},{"pos":[27670,27727],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IF A.200<ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;gt;</ph>0 AND A.200<ph id=\"ph2\">&amp;lt;</ph>10,000<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> (Complex statement)","source":"**IF A.200&gt;0 AND A.200&lt;10,000** (Complex statement)"},{"pos":[27732,27840],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IF A.200<ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;gt;</ph>10000 OR ((A.340/B.1200)<ph id=\"ph2\">\\*</ph>2 <ph id=\"ph3\">&amp;lt;</ph>1200)<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> (Complex statement that contains multiple expressions)","source":"**IF A.200&gt;10000 OR ((A.340/B.1200)\\*2 &lt;1200)** (Complex statement that contains multiple expressions)"},{"content":"The term <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Periods<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> in an <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>IF<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> statement represents the number of periods for the report.","pos":[27842,27934],"source":"The term **Periods** in an **IF** statement represents the number of periods for the report."},{"content":"This term is typically used to calculate a year-to-date average.","pos":[27935,27999]},{"content":"For example, when you run a report for period 7 YTD, the statement <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>B.150/Periods<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> means that the value in row 150 of column B is divided by 7.","pos":[28000,28145],"source":" For example, when you run a report for period 7 YTD, the statement **B.150/Periods** means that the value in row 150 of column B is divided by 7."},{"pos":[28152,28174],"content":"THEN and ELSE formulas","linkify":"THEN and ELSE formulas","nodes":[{"content":"THEN and ELSE formulas","pos":[0,22]}]},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>THEN<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>ELSE<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> formulas can be any valid calculation, from very simple value assignments to complex formulas.","pos":[28176,28296],"source":"The **THEN** and **ELSE** formulas can be any valid calculation, from very simple value assignments to complex formulas."},{"content":"For example, the statement <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IF A.200<ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;gt;</ph>0 THEN A=B.200<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> means, \"If the value in the cell in column A of row 200 is more than 0 (zero), put the value from the cell in column B of row 200 into the cell in column A of the current row.\"","pos":[28297,28531],"source":" For example, the statement **IF A.200&gt;0 THEN A=B.200** means, \"If the value in the cell in column A of row 200 is more than 0 (zero), put the value from the cell in column B of row 200 into the cell in column A of the current row.\""},{"content":"The preceding <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IF/THEN<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> statement puts a value in one column of the current row.","pos":[28532,28614],"source":" The preceding **IF/THEN** statement puts a value in one column of the current row."},{"content":"However, you can also use an at sign (@) in either true/false evaluations or the formula to represent all columns.","pos":[28615,28729]},{"content":"Here are some other examples that are described in the following sections:","pos":[28730,28804]},{"pos":[28810,28951],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IF A.200 <ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;gt;</ph>0 THEN B.200<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: If the value in cell A.200 is positive, the value from cell B.200 is put into every column of the current row.","source":"**IF A.200 &gt;0 THEN B.200**: If the value in cell A.200 is positive, the value from cell B.200 is put into every column of the current row."},{"pos":[28956,29120],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IF A.200 <ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;gt;</ph>0 THEN <ph id=\"ph2\">@200</ph><ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: If the value in cell A.200 is positive, the value from each column in row 200 is put into the corresponding column in the current row.","source":"**IF A.200 &gt;0 THEN @200**: If the value in cell A.200 is positive, the value from each column in row 200 is put into the corresponding column in the current row."},{"pos":[29125,29283],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IF <ph id=\"ph1\">@200</ph> <ph id=\"ph2\">&amp;gt;</ph>0 THEN <ph id=\"ph3\">@200</ph><ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: If the value in row 200 of the current column is positive, the value from row 200 is put into the same column in the current row.","source":"**IF @200 &gt;0 THEN @200**: If the value in row 200 of the current column is positive, the value from row 200 is put into the same column in the current row."},{"pos":[29289,29354],"content":"Restricting a calculation to a reporting unit in a row definition","linkify":"Restricting a calculation to a reporting unit in a row definition","nodes":[{"content":"Restricting a calculation to a reporting unit in a row definition","pos":[0,65]}]},{"content":"To restrict a calculation to a single reporting unit in a reporting tree, so that the resulting amount isn't rolled up to a higher-level unit, you can use the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt><ph id=\"ph1\">@Unit</ph><ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> code in the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Related Formulas/Rows/Units<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> cell in the row definition.","pos":[29356,29596],"source":"To restrict a calculation to a single reporting unit in a reporting tree, so that the resulting amount isn't rolled up to a higher-level unit, you can use the **@Unit** code in the **Related Formulas/Rows/Units** cell in the row definition."},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt><ph id=\"ph1\">@Unit</ph><ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> code is listed in column B of the reporting tree, <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Unit Name<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>.","pos":[29597,29675],"source":" The **@Unit** code is listed in column B of the reporting tree, **Unit Name**."},{"content":"When you use the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt><ph id=\"ph1\">@Unit</ph><ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> code, the values aren't rolled up, but the calculation is evaluated at every level of the reporting tree.","pos":[29676,29808],"source":" When you use the **@Unit** code, the values aren't rolled up, but the calculation is evaluated at every level of the reporting tree."},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> To use this function, a reporting tree must be associated with the row definition.","pos":[29809,29901],"source":"**Note:** To use this function, a reporting tree must be associated with the row definition."},{"content":"The calculation row can refer to a calculation row or a financial data row.","pos":[29902,29977]},{"content":"The calculation is recorded in the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Related Formulas/Rows/Units<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> cell of the row definition and the financial data–type restriction.","pos":[29978,30112],"source":" The calculation is recorded in the **Related Formulas/Rows/Units** cell of the row definition and the financial data–type restriction."},{"content":"The calculation must use a conditional calculation that starts with an <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IF <ph id=\"ph1\">@Unit</ph><ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> construction.","pos":[30113,30210],"source":" The calculation must use a conditional calculation that starts with an **IF @Unit** construction."},{"content":"Here is an example: IF <ph id=\"ph1\">@Unit</ph>(SALES) THEN <ph id=\"ph2\">@100</ph> ELSE 0 This calculation includes the amount from row 100 in every column of the report, but only for the SALES unit.","pos":[30211,30373],"source":" Here is an example: IF @Unit(SALES) THEN @100 ELSE 0 This calculation includes the amount from row 100 in every column of the report, but only for the SALES unit."},{"content":"If multiple units are named SALES, the amount appears in each of those units.","pos":[30374,30451]},{"content":"Additionally, row 100 can be a financial data row and can be defined as non-printing.","pos":[30452,30537]},{"content":"In this case, the amount is prevented from appearing in all units in the tree.","pos":[30538,30616]},{"content":"You can also limit the amount to a single column of the report, such as column H, by using a column restriction to print the value only in that column of the report.","pos":[30617,30782]},{"content":"You can include <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>OR<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> combinations in an <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>IF<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> statement.","pos":[30783,30842],"source":" You can include **OR** combinations in an **IF** statement."},{"content":"Here is an example: IF <ph id=\"ph1\">@Unit</ph>(SALES) OR <ph id=\"ph2\">@Unit</ph>(SALESWEST) THEN 5 ELSE <ph id=\"ph3\">@100</ph> You can specify a unit in a calculation-type restriction in one of the following ways:","pos":[30843,31002],"source":" Here is an example: IF @Unit(SALES) OR @Unit(SALESWEST) THEN 5 ELSE @100 You can specify a unit in a calculation-type restriction in one of the following ways:"},{"content":"Enter a unit name to include units that match.","pos":[31008,31054]},{"content":"For example, <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IF <ph id=\"ph1\">@Unit</ph>(SALES)<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> enables the calculation for any unit that is named SALES, even if there are several SALES units in the reporting tree.","pos":[31055,31206],"source":" For example, **IF @Unit(SALES)** enables the calculation for any unit that is named SALES, even if there are several SALES units in the reporting tree."},{"content":"Enter the company and unit name to restrict the calculation to specific units in a specific company.","pos":[31211,31311]},{"content":"For example, enter <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IF <ph id=\"ph1\">@Unit</ph>(ACME:SALES<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>) to restrict the calculation to SALES units in the ACME company.","pos":[31312,31419],"source":" For example, enter **IF @Unit(ACME:SALES**) to restrict the calculation to SALES units in the ACME company."},{"content":"Enter the full hierarchy code from the reporting tree to restrict the calculation to a specific unit.","pos":[31424,31525]},{"content":"For example, enter <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IF <ph id=\"ph1\">@Unit</ph>(SUMMARY^ACME^WEST COAST^SALES)<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.","pos":[31526,31589],"source":" For example, enter **IF @Unit(SUMMARY^ACME^WEST COAST^SALES)**."},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> To find the full hierarchy code, right-click in the reporting tree definition, and then select <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Copy Reporting Unit Identifier (H-code)<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>.","pos":[31590,31739],"source":"**Note:** To find the full hierarchy code, right-click in the reporting tree definition, and then select **Copy Reporting Unit Identifier (H-code)**."},{"pos":[31746,31788],"content":"Restrict a calculation to a reporting unit","linkify":"Restrict a calculation to a reporting unit","nodes":[{"content":"Restrict a calculation to a reporting unit","pos":[0,42]}]},{"pos":[31794,31884],"content":"In Report Designer, click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Row Definitions<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, and then open the row definition to modify.","source":"In Report Designer, click **Row Definitions**, and then open the row definition to modify."},{"pos":[31889,31952],"content":"Double-click the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Format Code<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> cell, and then select <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>CAL<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>.","source":"Double-click the **Format Code** cell, and then select **CAL**."},{"pos":[31957,32092],"content":"Click the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Related Formulas/Rows/Units<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> cell, and then enter a conditional calculation that starts with an <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>IF <ph id=\"ph1\">@Unit</ph><ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> construction.","source":"Click the **Related Formulas/Rows/Units** cell, and then enter a conditional calculation that starts with an **IF @Unit** construction."},{"pos":[32098,32144],"content":"IF/THEN/ELSE statements in a column definition","linkify":"IF/THEN/ELSE statements in a column definition","nodes":[{"content":"IF/THEN/ELSE statements in a column definition","pos":[0,46]}]},{"content":"An <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IF/THEN/ELSE<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> statement enables any calculation to depend on the results from any other column.","pos":[32146,32247],"source":"An **IF/THEN/ELSE** statement enables any calculation to depend on the results from any other column."},{"content":"You can refer to other columns, but you can't refer to a report cell in the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IF<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> statement.","pos":[32248,32341],"source":" You can refer to other columns, but you can't refer to a report cell in the **IF** statement."},{"content":"Any calculation must be applied to the whole column.","pos":[32342,32394]},{"content":"For example, the statement <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IF B<ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;gt;</ph>100 THEN B ELSE C<ph id=\"ph2\">\\*</ph>1.25<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> means, \"If the amount in column B is more than 100, put the value from column B into the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>CALC<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> column.","pos":[32395,32563],"source":" For example, the statement **IF B&gt;100 THEN B ELSE C\\*1.25** means, \"If the amount in column B is more than 100, put the value from column B into the **CALC** column."},{"content":"If the amount in column B isn't more than 100, multiply the value in column C by 1.25, and put the result into the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>CALC<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> column.\"","pos":[32564,32696],"source":" If the amount in column B isn't more than 100, multiply the value in column C by 1.25, and put the result into the **CALC** column.\""},{"content":"Always follow the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IF<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> statement with a logic statement that can be evaluated as true or false.","pos":[32697,32794],"source":" Always follow the **IF** statement with a logic statement that can be evaluated as true or false."},{"content":"The formulas that you use for both the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>THEN<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> statement and the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>ELSE<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> statement can contain references to any number of columns, and these formulas can be as complex as you want to make them.","pos":[32795,32991],"source":" The formulas that you use for both the **THEN** statement and the **ELSE** statement can contain references to any number of columns, and these formulas can be as complex as you want to make them."},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> You can't put the results of a calculation into any other column.","pos":[32992,33067],"source":"**Note:** You can't put the results of a calculation into any other column."},{"content":"The results must be in the column that contains the formula.","pos":[33068,33128]}]}